04:50.594 --> 04:52.030
I JUST CAME TO SAY SEE YA.

04:52.161 --> 04:53.554
-YOU GOT BODY BOARDS?

04:53.684 --> 04:54.685
-YEAH, ONE FOR TRICKS
AND ONE FOR SPEED.

04:54.816 --> 04:56.513
-I WISH I WAS GOING WITH YOU.

04:56.644 --> 04:57.862
-YEAH, I WISH YOU WERE TOO.

04:57.993 --> 04:59.647
WE'RE GONNA GET
THE BIG OL' TROPHY,

04:59.777 --> 05:01.605
AND ALL THE A&W WE
CAN DRINK FOR A YEAR.

05:01.736 --> 05:04.478
-YOU BETTER WIN, 'CAUSE
I LOVE THAT CREAM SODA.

05:04.608 --> 05:06.306
-ALL RIGHT, I'LL DO
IT JUST FOR YOU.

05:06.436 --> 05:07.611
-OKAY, YOU CALL ME WHEN YOU
GET TO SANTA BARBARA, HUH?

05:07.742 --> 05:09.004
-ALL RIGHT, I WILL. I LOVE YOU.

05:09.134 --> 05:11.006
-LOVE YOU, TOO. GOOD LUCK.

05:11.136 --> 05:12.877
HEY BRING ME BACK ONE
OF THOSE T-SHIRTS, HUH?

05:13.008 --> 05:14.270
-ALL RIGHT. I WILL.

05:32.854 --> 05:34.943
-HEY, YOU SURE
THIS IS THE PLACE?

05:35.073 --> 05:37.119
-YEAH, I ONCE PASSED
IT WITH MITCH.

05:37.249 --> 05:38.860
HE SAID THAT HE AND HIS BROTHER
USED TO SURF HERE
TO SETTLE THINGS.

05:38.990 --> 05:40.427
-HOW'S THAT?

05:40.557 --> 05:43.125
-FIRST ONE WHO WIPES
OUT ON THE ROCKS, LOSES.

05:43.995 --> 05:45.475
-SO WHAT ABOUT LEASHES?

05:45.606 --> 05:46.824
-WE DON'T USE THEM.

05:47.695 --> 05:50.045
-HEY, MATT, YOU KNOW HOW
MUCH THIS BOARD COSTS?

05:50.175 --> 05:51.438
-HEY, YOU WANT TO FORFEIT?

05:52.700 --> 05:55.267
-OKAY, SO, CLOSEST TO THE
ROCK WITHOUT WIPING OUT WINS.

05:55.398 --> 05:56.660
IS THAT RIGHT?

05:57.748 --> 05:59.184
LOSER LAYS OFF SUMMER?

06:00.185 --> 06:01.926
-AND IF WE BOTH WIPE OUT,

06:02.057 --> 06:03.406
WE BOTH LAY OFF SUMMER.

06:03.537 --> 06:05.495
-OKAY, SO WHAT IF
NEITHER OF US WIPES OUT?

06:06.104 --> 06:07.454
-WE'LL HAVE TO
FIND SOMETHING ELSE.

06:41.531 --> 06:42.837
-SUMMER, COME ON, HOP IN.

06:43.794 --> 06:44.752
-I NEED TO WORK OUT.

06:45.361 --> 06:46.971
-YOU'VE WORKED OUT LONG ENOUGH.

06:47.711 --> 06:49.887
-I JUST HAVE 200
MORE CALORIES TO BURN.

06:50.018 --> 06:51.846
-YOU'RE THIN, SUMMER.
YOU'RE THIN.

06:51.976 --> 06:53.456
NOW WILL YOU STOP
WORRYING ABOUT IT.

06:53.587 --> 06:55.850
AND GET IN THE TRUCK, NOW!

07:18.873 --> 07:20.091
DID YOU HAVE BREAKFAST
THIS MORNING?

07:20.222 --> 07:21.179
-YES.

07:21.745 --> 07:23.268
-DID YOU BINGE AND PURGE?

07:23.834 --> 07:24.748
-NO.

07:28.186 --> 07:31.451
LOOK, CJ, IF WE'RE NOT GONNA
DRIVE, I'LL JUST RUN, OKAY?

07:32.713 --> 07:34.192
-DID YOU GO TO THAT
CLINIC I TOLD YOU ABOUT?

07:34.323 --> 07:36.151
-LOOK, CJ, FOR THE LAST TIME,

07:36.281 --> 07:39.023
I DO NOT HAVE AN
EATING DISORDER, OKAY?

07:39.154 --> 07:40.590
YOU JUST DON'T KNOW
THE KIND OF PRESSURE

07:40.721 --> 07:42.157
THAT MATT AND SLADE
HAVE BEEN PUTTING ON ME.

07:42.287 --> 07:44.333
-OH, I KNOW ALL ABOUT
THE KIND OF PRESSURE

07:44.464 --> 07:46.640
THAT MEN PUT US UNDER.
BELIEVE ME,

07:47.249 --> 07:50.078
AND THAT IS NOT THE PROBLEM.

07:50.208 --> 07:51.906
-OH, YEAH? THEN WHAT IS?

07:53.081 --> 07:53.951
-YOU'RE BULIMIC.

07:54.082 --> 07:55.562
-I AM NOT BULIMIC.

07:55.692 --> 07:56.606
-AND YOU'RE IN DENIAL.

07:56.737 --> 07:57.694
-OH.

07:59.174 --> 08:02.133
-SUMMER, WAKE UP. THERE ARE
PEOPLE THAT CAN HELP YOU.

08:02.264 --> 08:03.221
YOU COULD DIE FROM THIS.

08:03.352 --> 08:04.440
-[SCOFF].

09:29.220 --> 09:30.134
[YELLS]

10:02.340 --> 10:03.254
-HAVE YOU SEEN MY BOARD?

10:03.385 --> 10:04.821
-NO.

10:06.127 --> 10:07.128
-PIECES OF IT?

10:07.258 --> 10:08.433
-NOPE.

10:14.048 --> 10:15.049
-WHERE'D IT GO?

11:02.357 --> 11:03.837
-MITCH.

11:03.967 --> 11:05.316
-YEAH.
-CAN I TALK TO YOU?

11:05.447 --> 11:06.796
-SURE, WHAT'S UP?

11:07.884 --> 11:09.277
-I'M WORRIED ABOUT SUMMER.

11:09.407 --> 11:11.758
SHE HAS ALL THE CLASSIC
SIGNS OF BULIMIA,

11:12.672 --> 11:14.064
AND I'M AFRAID
THAT'S GONNA AFFECT

11:14.195 --> 11:15.326
HER ABILITY TO LIFE GUARD.

11:16.414 --> 11:18.025
-CJ, SHE SEEMS FINE TO ME.

11:18.155 --> 11:19.417
I HAVEN'T NOTICED ANYTHING.

11:19.548 --> 11:20.941
-WELL PEOPLE WITH
EATING DISORDERS

11:21.071 --> 11:22.769
ARE MASTERS AT HIDING IT.

11:23.683 --> 11:25.206
IT SAPS YOUR STRENGTH.

11:26.468 --> 11:28.296
SHE COULD PASS OUT
DURING A RESCUE.

11:29.036 --> 11:31.386
-CAN'T PULL HER OFF DUTY JUST
BECAUSE YOU'RE SUSPICIOUS.

11:35.042 --> 11:36.913
-MITCH, I KNOW
ABOUT THESE THINGS.

11:37.044 --> 11:39.002
I'VE GONE THROUGH IT.

11:39.916 --> 11:43.703
I WENT THROUGH A YEAR OF
HELL BINGING AND PURGING.

11:45.792 --> 11:48.055
IT'S LIKE BEING AN
ALCOHOLIC BUT WITH FOOD.

11:49.752 --> 11:51.493
-I'M SORRY, CJ. I NEVER KNEW.

11:52.363 --> 11:54.714
-WELL IT'S NOT SOMETHING
I GO AROUND TELLING PEOPLE.

11:54.844 --> 11:58.108
BUT I GOT HELP, AND I THINK
THAT'S WHAT SUMMER NEEDS TOO.

11:58.239 --> 12:00.545
DO YOU THINK YOU
COULD TALK TO HER?

12:00.676 --> 12:01.851
-ABSOLUTELY.

12:05.463 --> 12:08.118
-OH, AND DO YOU THINK YOU CAN
TALK TO MATT AND SLADE, TOO?

12:08.249 --> 12:10.164
THEY'RE PUTTING A LOT
OF PRESSURE ON SUMMER.

12:10.294 --> 12:11.731
-OKAY.

12:16.823 --> 12:19.260
HEY, GUYS, HOW WAS
SURFING THIS MORNING?

12:19.390 --> 12:22.045
-MITCH, YOU WON'T BELIEVE IT.
WE SURFED WHITE WATER COVE.

12:22.176 --> 12:24.178
-YEAH AND MATT WIPED OUT.

12:24.308 --> 12:26.746
-MY BOARD DISAPPEARED. I MEAN,
IT HIT THE ROCKS,
AND IT WAS GONE.

12:27.616 --> 12:28.573
-HAPPENS OUT THERE.

12:28.704 --> 12:29.879
-HOW?

12:30.010 --> 12:31.576
-WHAT DO YOU THINK
HAPPENED TO IT?

12:31.707 --> 12:33.100
-I DON'T KNOW. THERE'S
SOME SORT OF UNDERCURRENT,

12:33.230 --> 12:35.406
PULLS THE BOARDS DOWN
INTO SOME KIND OF CAVE.

12:35.537 --> 12:38.627
OLD TIME SURFERS CALL IT
THE SURFBOARD BURIAL GROUND.

12:38.758 --> 12:40.411
-YOU EVER GONE IN IT?

12:40.542 --> 12:42.413
-NO, I HAVEN'T. YOU GOTTA
FREE DIVE TO GET IN THERE,

12:42.544 --> 12:44.415
BUT BEN WENT IN THERE ONCE.

12:45.112 --> 12:47.723
SAID HE FOUND ONE OF DUKE
KAHANAMOKU'S OLD LONG BOARDS.

12:47.854 --> 12:49.116
-WHOA.

12:49.594 --> 12:51.248
-LISTEN, THAT'S NOT WHY I CAME.

12:51.379 --> 12:53.773
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU
GUYS ABOUT SUMMER.

12:58.865 --> 13:00.823
-SHE'S THE FASTEST
MINI JET BOAT THERE IS.

13:05.001 --> 13:06.698
-IS IT TRACEABLE?

13:06.829 --> 13:08.657
-NO, YOU GOT THE CASH?

13:13.618 --> 13:15.142
-DON'T WORRY. IT'S ALL THERE.

13:15.272 --> 13:17.100
-LADY, YOU JUST
BOUGHT YOURSELF A BOAT.

13:17.231 --> 13:19.450
-SO I'M COUNTING ON YOU
GUYS NOT TO PRESSURE SUMMER.

13:19.581 --> 13:20.930
ARE WE CLEAR?

13:21.061 --> 13:22.932
-MITCH, SLADE AND
I WORKED THINGS OUT.

13:23.063 --> 13:24.760
I'M GONNA BACK OFF.

13:24.891 --> 13:26.849
-SHE NEEDS HER SPACE.
YOU BACK OFF, TOO, ALL RIGHT?

13:26.980 --> 13:29.069
-OKAY.
-OKAY GUYS, THANKS A LOT.

13:29.199 --> 13:30.331
-SEE YA LATER.

13:36.250 --> 13:37.294
-SO WHAT DO YOU
THINK WE SHOULD DO?

13:37.425 --> 13:38.948
-RIGHT NOW?

13:39.079 --> 13:40.341
I WANT TO GO FIND THAT
CAVE AND CHECK IT OUT.

13:40.471 --> 13:42.604
-YEAH, I WANT TO
FIND MY SURF BOARD.

13:42.734 --> 13:44.084
BUT THERE'S NO TIME TODAY.

13:44.214 --> 13:45.912
WE'LL HAVE TO DIVE AND
FIND THE CAVE TOMORROW.

13:46.042 --> 13:47.522
-ALL RIGHT.

13:51.178 --> 13:53.528
-ATTENTION, PRISONERS.
VISITING HOURS

13:53.658 --> 13:56.661
FOR CELL BLOCK C WILL
START IN FIVE MINUTES.

13:56.792 --> 13:59.751
VISITING HOURS FOR CELL BLOCK
C WILL START IN FIVE MINUTES.

