-HE'S IN THE WATER.

19:32.736 --> 19:34.129
-THERE HE IS.

19:34.260 --> 19:35.609
-DON'T LET HIM GET AWAY.

19:36.392 --> 19:37.350
-OPEN FIRE.

20:13.429 --> 20:14.735
-BRADY!

20:20.610 --> 20:22.569
COME ON, BABY. YOU'RE OUT.

20:22.699 --> 20:24.135
COME ON, HANG ON.

20:24.266 --> 20:26.312
COME ON, BRADY. WE'RE TOGETHER.

20:27.182 --> 20:29.053
WE'RE TOGETHER. COME ON.

20:39.803 --> 20:42.415
-ONE OF THE PRISON GUARDS IS
SURE HE WOUNDED THE ESCAPEE

20:42.545 --> 20:44.591
SO THEY MAY NOT HAVE GOTTEN FAR.

20:44.721 --> 20:46.201
-WHO ARE THESE CHARACTERS?

20:46.332 --> 20:48.551
-DEBRA HARRIS AND BRADY NICKELS.

20:49.335 --> 20:51.554
HAVE YOUR LIFE GUARDS BE
ON THE LOOKOUT FOR THEM.

20:51.685 --> 20:52.599
-WHAT'S THEIR STORY?

20:52.729 --> 20:54.470
-WELL SHE CONNED RICH MEN.

20:54.601 --> 20:56.124
ONCE THEY BROUGHT HER HOME,
SHE'D PINPOINT THEIR VALUABLES,

20:56.255 --> 20:57.604
HE'D COME IN AND ROB THEM.

20:57.734 --> 20:58.779
A COUPLE OF THEIR
MARKS ENDED UP DEAD.

21:00.781 --> 21:03.000
-SO WHO DID 'EM IN, HIM OR HER?

21:03.697 --> 21:05.176
-WELL, HE TOOK THE FALL FOR IT,
BUT A LOT OF PEOPLE

21:05.307 --> 21:06.700
THINK SHE WAS THE REAL KILLER.

21:41.648 --> 21:42.910
-LISTEN, SUMMER,
WE NEED TO TALK.

21:43.040 --> 21:44.346
-MATT.

21:45.347 --> 21:48.219
-THIS MORNING, SLADE AND I
WORKED THINGS OUT. WE--

21:48.350 --> 21:50.700
-OH DON'T EVEN TELL ME.
I DON'T WANT TO KNOW.

21:52.702 --> 21:56.053
LISTEN, MATT, I JUST WANT US TO
BE FRIENDS AGAIN. ALL OF US.

21:56.184 --> 21:59.013
I WANT TO GO AND
DO THINGS TOGETHER.

21:59.143 --> 22:00.710
YOU KNOW, HAVE FUN
THE WAY WE USED TO.

22:03.234 --> 22:04.758
LET'S JUST GO BACK
TO WAY THINGS WERE

22:04.888 --> 22:06.281
WHEN WE ALL FIRST MET, PLEASE?

22:06.412 --> 22:10.154
-HEY, THAT'S OKAY WITH ME.
REALLY, IT IS.

22:11.895 --> 22:13.767
I JUST NEVER WANT TO
LOSE YOUR FRIENDSHIP.

22:14.507 --> 22:16.247
-THANK YOU, MATT.

22:16.378 --> 22:18.337
I DON'T EVER WANT TO
LOSE YOURS EITHER.

22:19.381 --> 22:21.296
I'M GONNA TALK TO SLADE AND THEN

22:21.427 --> 22:23.951
MAYBE WE CAN ALL GO OUT
AND DO SOMETHING FUN.

22:25.431 --> 22:27.215
-WELL, WHY DON'T YOU COME
WITH US TOMORROW MORNING.

22:27.346 --> 22:28.782
-WHERE?

22:28.912 --> 22:30.740
-WE'RE GOING TO THE SURF
BOARD BURIAL GROUNDS.

22:30.871 --> 22:32.263
-WHERE?

22:32.394 --> 22:34.440
-JUST COME WITH US. YOU'LL SEE.

22:47.278 --> 22:48.671
-THAT'S GOOD. RIGHT THERE.

22:52.283 --> 22:53.459
-OW.

22:56.462 --> 23:00.291
-HANG ON, BRADY.
HANG ON. HANG ON.

23:00.422 --> 23:03.033
OKAY. OKAY. OKAY.

23:04.165 --> 23:05.558
I GOTTA GET YOU TO A DOCTOR.

23:05.688 --> 23:08.822
-NO, I'D RATHER DIE THAN
GO BACK TO THAT PRISON.

23:08.952 --> 23:11.346
-IF YOU DIE,
I DON'T WANT TO LIVE.

23:11.477 --> 23:14.393
I WON'T LIVE WITHOUT YOU
ANYMORE, BRADY. I WON'T DO IT.

23:15.437 --> 23:17.265
-WHY ISN'T THIS BOAT MOVING?

23:17.396 --> 23:19.267
WHY AREN'T WE OUT TO SEA YET?

23:20.399 --> 23:22.401
-I TOLD THE CAPTAIN TO
STAY HERE UNTIL I GOT --
-OH --

23:22.531 --> 23:24.620
-COME ON, BABY.
YOU GOTTA HANG ON.

23:24.751 --> 23:27.144
I'M GONNA GET SOMEONE
WHO CAN HELP YOU.

23:27.275 --> 23:30.147
SOMEONE WHO CAN GET THAT
BULLET OUT, ALL RIGHT?
COME ON. YOU GOTTA HANG ON.

24:11.406 --> 24:13.887
-TWO WAVE RUNNERS IN TWO DAYS.

24:14.017 --> 24:16.367
IT'S NOT GONNA LOOK GOOD
ON THE BUDGET REPORT.

24:17.281 --> 24:20.502
AH, I GOT IT. I'LL GET
STEPHANIE TO SIGN IT.

24:22.504 --> 24:24.288
OH, PURCHASE ORDER.

24:49.792 --> 24:50.793
HEY!

24:55.015 --> 24:56.886
WHAT THE HELL ARE
YOU DOING HERE?

25:02.544 --> 25:05.416
-GET ON THE BOAT. NOW, MOVE.

25:25.393 --> 25:28.004
NOW STOP. RIGHT THERE. STOP.

25:28.962 --> 25:30.137
PUT EVERYTHING DOWN.

25:31.617 --> 25:32.835
MOVE!

25:45.761 --> 25:46.675
HELP HIM.

25:48.982 --> 25:50.244
-PUT THE GUN DOWN FIRST.

25:50.374 --> 25:52.202
-THIS ISN'T A NEGOTIATION.

25:52.333 --> 25:53.987
IF HE DIES SO DO YOU.

25:54.117 --> 25:55.292
-IF I DIE, SO WILL HE.

25:55.423 --> 25:56.990
-DON'T PLAY GAMES WITH ME.

25:58.165 --> 25:59.340
I KNOW WHAT YOUR JOB REQUIRES,

25:59.470 --> 26:00.733
AND YOU HAVE TO
DO THE RIGHT THING

26:00.863 --> 26:02.212
NO MATTER WHAT THE SITUATION.

26:02.343 --> 26:04.824
SO STOP WASTING TIME
AND SAVE HIS LIFE,

26:05.476 --> 26:06.913
AND YOUR OWN.

26:07.043 --> 26:08.610
-YOU KNOW, THERE WILL BE
PEOPLE LOOKING FOR ME.

26:08.741 --> 26:10.569
-WELL, YOU JUST LET
ME WORRY ABOUT THAT.

26:14.181 --> 26:15.095
HELP HIM.

26:22.058 --> 26:23.582
HE'S DYING.

26:45.299 --> 26:46.735
WHAT IS THIS? A BULLET WOUND?

26:46.866 --> 26:48.084
-YEAH.

26:48.737 --> 26:49.651
-HOW LONG AGO?

26:49.782 --> 26:51.566
-ALMOST THREE HOURS AGO.

26:52.828 --> 26:53.960
-HE'S LOST A LOT OF BLOOD.

26:54.090 --> 26:55.222
YOU GOTTA GET HIM TO A HOSPITAL.

26:55.352 --> 26:56.179
-THAT'S NOT AN OPTION.

26:56.310 --> 26:57.877
-I'M NOT A SURGEON.

26:58.007 --> 26:59.661
-IF YOU HAVE THAT EQUIPMENT,
YOU KNOW HOW TO USE IT.

26:59.792 --> 27:02.882
SO USE IT. USE IT NOW.

27:13.022 --> 27:14.589
-YOU'RE TRYING TO TELL
ME THAT YOU EXPECT ME

27:14.720 --> 27:16.330
TO PULL A BULLET OUT
OF THIS GUY OUT AT SEA?

27:16.460 --> 27:18.462
-DON'T YOU DARE
UNDERESTIMATE HOW IMPORTANT

27:18.593 --> 27:21.030
HIS LIFE IS TO ME, AND
HOW UNIMPORTANT YOURS IS.

27:21.770 --> 27:25.252
HELP HIM, OR I SWEAR
IT, I'LL KILL YOU.

27:25.382 --> 27:27.602
-JUST TAKE IT EASY, HUH?

27:29.256 --> 27:34.653
I GOT A SON. HIS NAME IS HOBIE.
HE'S 12 YEARS OLD.

27:36.567 --> 27:38.482
-WELL WE HAVE A SON NAMED SETH,

27:39.658 --> 27:41.485
AND HE'S FIVE YEARS OLD,

27:43.923 --> 27:48.405
AND HIS FATHER'S DYING.
HELP HIM.

28:13.082 --> 28:15.345
-SUMMER ARE YOU
SURE YOU'RE ALL RIGHT?

28:15.476 --> 28:18.218
-YEAH I'M FINE.
I'M WITH MY TWO BEST FRIENDS.

28:18.348 --> 28:19.262
WHAT COULD BE WRONG?

28:20.176 --> 28:21.830
-I DON'T KNOW. YOU JUST LOOK
A LITTLE PALE, THAT'S ALL.

28:24.311 --> 28:25.921
MAYBE YOU BETTER STAY HERE.

28:26.052 --> 28:27.357
-OH, NO, I'M GONNA BE ALL RIGHT
ONCE I HIT THE WATER.

28:27.488 --> 28:28.358
IT'LL REVIVE ME.

28:29.185 --> 28:31.100
-JUST TRYING TO LOOK OUT
FOR MY FRIEND, THAT'S ALL.

28:31.884 --> 28:33.537
-SLADE, THANKS FOR
AGREEING TO DO THIS.

28:36.279 --> 28:37.498
-ARE YOU READY?

28:37.628 --> 28:39.152
-YEAH, LET'S DO IT.

29:42.650 --> 29:45.000
-ALL RIGHT. GET READY.

29:55.228 --> 29:57.143
ONE, TWO--

30:53.895 --> 30:55.288
WOW.

31:07.866 --> 31:08.823
-WOW.

31:12.174 --> 31:14.046
LOOK AT THIS PLACE.

31:14.698 --> 31:16.309
THERE'S MY BOARD.

31:18.615 --> 31:19.703
WHERE'S THE OTHER ONE?

31:21.053 --> 31:24.883
WHOA!
-WHAT WAS THAT ALL ABOUT?

31:27.624 --> 31:28.887
CHECK IT OUT.

31:30.410 --> 31:32.281
THIS BOARD MUST BE 30 YEARS OLD.

31:32.412 --> 31:34.544
-YOU GUYS, I HOPE WE
CAN MAKE IT OUT OF HERE.

31:34.675 --> 31:36.764
THIS CURRENT IS REALLY STRONG.

31:37.896 --> 31:39.549
-THIS LOOKS LIKE AN
OLD '50'S LONG BOARD.

31:59.439 --> 32:01.615
-WHAT WAS THAT? I FELT
SOMETHING TOUCH MY LEG.

32:02.137 --> 32:03.443
-IT'S JUST SEAWEED.

32:04.966 --> 32:06.054
-NO, IT FELT LIKE --

32:07.490 --> 32:08.927
-SUMMER!

32:52.579 --> 32:54.929
[GASPING]

33:00.239 --> 33:01.892
HEY, LET'S GET
SUMMER OUT OF HERE.

33:03.416 --> 33:04.330
-YOU ALL RIGHT?

33:04.460 --> 33:05.287
-I'M NOT GONNA MAKE IT.

33:05.418 --> 33:06.985
-YES YOU CAN.

33:07.115 --> 33:09.639
YOU CAN MAKE IT, COME ON.
WE'LL DO IT TOGETHER.

33:09.770 --> 33:11.902
HOLD YOUR BREATH FOR 20 SECONDS.

33:12.033 --> 33:13.992
ONE, TWO --

33:14.122 --> 33:15.384
-[SCREAMING]

33:32.053 --> 33:33.576
-[GASPING]

34:07.654 --> 34:09.264
-MATT!

34:09.395 --> 34:10.438
-GET OUT, NOW!

34:11.440 --> 34:12.702
-MATT!

34:15.139 --> 34:16.489
MATT!

34:43.081 --> 34:44.864
MATT! MATT!

34:45.692 --> 34:47.955
NO, I'VE GOT TO GO BACK
IN AND HELP HIM!

34:49.217 --> 34:50.697
HELP HIM!

34:50.827 --> 34:51.828
-NO, YOU'RE TOO WEAK.
I GOTTA STAY WITH YOU.

34:51.958 --> 34:53.786
-NO, I DON'T CARE! GO!

34:53.917 --> 34:55.658
PLEASE! GO, PLEASE!

35:01.186 --> 35:04.319
I LOVE YOU. I LOVE YOU SO MUCH.

35:07.322 --> 35:08.715
-I'M HERE.

35:11.326 --> 35:12.806
IT'S OKAY.

35:21.945 --> 35:23.425
-YOU WANT YOUR
BOYFRIEND TO LIVE,

35:23.556 --> 35:25.210
YOU BETTER TELL THE
CAPTAIN TO STOP THE SHIP.

35:26.733 --> 35:29.475
-DROP ANCHOR. DO IT.
-NOW?

35:29.605 --> 35:31.172
YES, MA'AM.

35:39.049 --> 35:40.268
-OKAY, I'M GONNA NEED
YOUR HELP HERE.

35:41.878 --> 35:43.053
I NEED YOUR HELP.

35:46.144 --> 35:47.884
GRAB SOME GAUZE.
PUT IT ON THE WOUND.

35:50.322 --> 35:52.193
COME ON, HOLD IT TIGHT.
ALL RIGHT.

35:53.760 --> 35:55.283
I NEED BOTH HANDS.

35:56.980 --> 35:58.808
COME ON, I NEED BOTH HANDS.

36:00.158 --> 36:02.377
GRAB THE SODIUM CHLORIDE.
IT'S IN THAT BOTTLE RIGHT THERE.

37:27.810 --> 37:30.944
-COME ON, SLADE.
DON'T GO TO HAWAII MAN.

37:32.075 --> 37:33.120
STAY HERE.

37:33.251 --> 37:35.949
-NAH, YOU TWO BELONG TOGETHER.

37:36.645 --> 37:37.820
I'M JUST GONNA GO HANG OUT

37:37.951 --> 37:38.778
ON THE NORTH SHORE
FOR THE WINTER.

37:38.908 --> 37:39.735
YOU SHOULD COME VISIT.

37:39.866 --> 37:41.650
-WE'RE GONNA MISS YOU.

37:45.306 --> 37:46.916
-YOU GUYS TAKE
CARE OF EACH OTHER.

37:48.788 --> 37:49.876
-WE WILL.

37:53.880 --> 37:54.837
SEE YOU LATER.

37:54.968 --> 37:56.099
-ALL RIGHT.

38:09.548 --> 38:14.944
[BOTH LAUGHING]

38:17.164 --> 38:18.992
-I LOVE THIS BEACH SO MUCH.

38:21.429 --> 38:22.648
LOOK AT THIS.

38:24.127 --> 38:25.259
-[LAUGHS]

38:25.912 --> 38:27.261
WHAT'S SO FUNNY?

38:27.392 --> 38:29.829
-OH, JUST THINKING
ABOUT ALMOST BEING

38:29.959 --> 38:32.222
THAT OCTOPUS' DINNER HAS MADE ME

38:32.353 --> 38:34.790
LOOK AT FOOD IN SUCH
A DIFFERENT WAY.

38:37.445 --> 38:38.707
-IN WHAT WAY?

38:39.229 --> 38:40.927
-I DON'T KNOW, JUST DIFFERENT.

38:41.971 --> 38:43.321
IT'S NOT SOMETHING TO FILL UP ON

38:43.451 --> 38:44.800
WHEN YOU'RE FEELING EMPTY.

38:47.586 --> 38:48.630
MATT...

38:52.895 --> 38:54.854
THERE'S SOMEWHERE I'D LIKE
YOU TO GO WITH ME TOMORROW.

38:55.507 --> 38:56.508
-SURE, WHERE?

38:57.857 --> 38:59.859
-JUST THIS PLACE
THAT CJ SUGGESTED:

39:00.599 --> 39:02.340
AN EATING DISORDERS CLINIC,

39:04.037 --> 39:05.865
BUT IT WOULD REALLY MEAN A LOT
TO ME IF YOU WERE THERE.

39:05.995 --> 39:08.041
-THEN THAT'S WHERE I'LL BE.

39:20.880 --> 39:22.055
-SCISSORS.

39:31.412 --> 39:32.718
[EXHALES]

39:45.121 --> 39:46.427
WHAT, ARE YOU GONNA
SHOOT ME NOW?

39:47.210 --> 39:49.212
-WERE YOU GONNA STAB
ME WITH THOSE SCISSORS?

39:49.343 --> 39:51.911
-NO, I'M IN THE BUSINESS OF
SAVING LIVES, NOT TAKING THEM.

39:52.825 --> 39:54.217
-DON'T TELL ME YOU
WEREN'T THINKING ABOUT IT.

39:54.348 --> 39:56.089
-YOU MEAN FIGHTING
FOR MY OWN LIFE?

39:56.219 --> 39:57.177
YEAH, THAT THOUGHT'S
CROSSED MY MIND.

39:58.004 --> 39:59.353
-YOU WANT TO LIVE?

39:59.484 --> 40:00.485
THEN DON'T TRY ANYTHING HEROIC.

40:00.615 --> 40:02.008
-YOU WANT HIM TO LIVE?

40:02.138 --> 40:03.401
-OH, HE'D BETTER LIVE.

40:03.531 --> 40:05.011
-HE BETTER GET TO A HOSPITAL.

40:05.141 --> 40:06.578
-AND GO BACK TO PRISON?

40:07.448 --> 40:08.449
NO.

40:09.145 --> 40:10.625
HE'S A FREE SPIRIT.

40:11.191 --> 40:12.714
HE CAN'T BE CAGED.

40:12.845 --> 40:14.847
-HOW'D YOU GET INVOLVED
IN ALL THIS, ANYWAY?

40:16.762 --> 40:18.154
-HE RESCUED ME.

40:18.285 --> 40:19.373
-FROM WHAT?

40:19.504 --> 40:20.896
-FROM A DULL BORING LIFE.

40:21.027 --> 40:23.986
-[LAUGHS] THERE ARE
A LOT OF OTHER WAYS

40:24.117 --> 40:26.206
OF FEELING ALIVE THAN
BEING A CRIMINAL.

40:26.336 --> 40:28.426
-YEAH, I'M SURE THERE ARE.

40:28.556 --> 40:30.906
BUT IT'S LITTLE TO
LATE TO TRY TO GO BACK
AND FIND THEM NOW ISN'T IT?

40:31.037 --> 40:32.604
-NO, IT'S NEVER TOO LATE.

40:32.734 --> 40:34.954
-ONCE YOU PASS THAT POINT,
THERE'S NO GOING BACK.

40:37.043 --> 40:38.131
-HAVE WE?

40:39.132 --> 40:40.002
-HAVE WE WHAT?

40:41.134 --> 40:42.352
-PASSED THAT POINT.

40:47.575 --> 40:50.317
-I DON'T KNOW, MAYBE.

40:53.929 --> 40:54.974
MAYBE NOT.

41:08.857 --> 41:10.859
[ENDING THEME PLAYING]
